{"ts": "2026-06-07T21:04:13.572684+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "## Summary\n\n### Package Manager\nThis repository uses **Yarn** (classic v1) as its package manager. Evidence:\n- A `yarn.lock` file (542 KB) is present in the root.\n- All project scripts in `package.json` use `yarn` (e.g., `\"fix\": \"yarn lint --fix\"`).\n- The `Taskfile.yaml` explicitly runs `yarn install`, `yarn release`, etc.\n\n> Note: The Taskfile's `init` task also installs some global CLI tools via `npm install -g`, but the project's own dependency management is done through **yarn**.\n\n---\n\n### Environment-Specific Script Names\n\n#### From `package.json` (npm/yarn scripts)\n\n| Script | Command | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| `dev` | `cross-env NODE_ENV=local vite --host` | Start local dev server (`local` env) |\n| `dev:stg` | `cross-env NODE_ENV=stg vite` | Start dev server for staging |\n| `serve` | `vite preview --host` | Preview the built production bundle locally |\n| `build` | `vite build --mode prod` | Build for production (`prod` mode) |\n| `build:stg` | `cross-env vite build --mode test` | Build for staging (`test` mode) |\n| `build:prod` | `cross-env vite build --mode production` | Build for production (`production` mode) |\n| `deploy` | `gh-pages -d dist` | Deploy the `dist` folder to GitHub Pages |\n| `lint` | `eslint --ext .jsx,.js,.ts,.tsx .` | Run ESLint across the project |\n| `fix` | `yarn lint --fix` | Auto-fix lint issues |\n\n#### From `Taskfile.yaml` (Task runner scripts)\n\n| Task | Command | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| `init` | `npm install -g … && cp envs/.env.local .env && yarn install` | One-time project initialisation (global CLI tools + local env + dependencies) |\n| `changelog` | `conventional-changelog -p angular -i CHANGELOG.md -s -r 0` | Generate a changelog from conventional commits |\n| `release` | `git fetch && yarn release && task changelog && git add . && git cz` | Full release workflow (fetch, version, changelog, commit) |\n| `commit` | `git add . && git cz && git push` | Stage all changes, commit via Commitizen, and push |\n\n#### Environment configuration files (`envs/`)\n\nThe repository provides per-environment `.env` files that are consumed by the scripts above:\n\n- `envs/.env.local` — Local development (NODE_ENV=local, VITE_BUILD_ENV=development)\n- `envs/.env.stg` — Staging (NODE_ENV=stg, VITE_BUILD_ENV=production)\n- `envs/.env.prod` — Production (NODE_ENV=prod, VITE_BUILD_ENV=production)\n\nThe `init` task copies `.env.local` → `.env` as the default environment configuration.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 1039, "prompt_tokens": 6464, "total_tokens": 7503, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 335, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": null, "cached_tokens": 6016}, "prompt_cache_hit_tokens": 6016, "prompt_cache_miss_tokens": 448}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "deepseek-v4-flash", "system_fingerprint": "fp_8b330d02d0_prod0820_fp8_kvcache_20260402", "id": "a5cba406-28ab-4266-abba-0ce8ae8b48c7", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea3e6-5e76-79b0-8bed-64055c10e0a1-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 6464, "output_tokens": 1039, "total_tokens": 7503, "input_token_details": {"cache_read": 6016}, "output_token_details": {"reasoning": 335}}}}]}}}
